git status🌟 Shows the current status of the repository, such as untracked files, changes to be committed, etc.
⚠️ Note: Always start with git status to check the current state of your working directory.

git add .🔲 Stages all the changes in your working directory for the next commit.

git commit -m "improving share design"✍️ Commits the staged changes with a commit message explaining the change.

git pull origin branch-name⬇️ Pulls the latest changes from the remote repository for the specified branch.
🔧 command: git pull origin branch-name should specify the branch name.
📌 Example: git pull origin share-favourites1
⚠️ Note: Make sure to specify the correct branch. In this case, "share-favourites1".

git push origin share-favourites1⬆️ Pushes the committed changes to the specified remote branch.
⚠️ Note: This command uploads your local commits to the remote repository.

git branch🌿 Lists all the branches in your local repository.
📍 Note: This shows which branch you are currently on and all the other branches.

git checkout branch-name🔄 Switches to the specified branch 
📌 Example: git checkout share-favourites2
⚠️ Note: Always ensure you're on the correct branch before making changes.

clear🧹 Clears the terminal screen.
⚠️ Note: This is not a git command, but a terminal command used to clear the screen.
